The bird is responding to a nearby oriental reed warbler with a churr call of 0.3 to 0.4s duration.  The first churr can be heard at 20s.  

The video recording from which this audio is extracted is here, 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oh6IqaLCr0U

Other recordings of this same vagrant individual have been posted by Lim Kim Chuan, XC400748, XC400749, and Yong Ding Li XC400778.  Those recordings do not have this churr call.

Behaviour: the bird alternated loud song with more mumbled strophes (as in recording), while perched rather prominently in various crowns of the willow shoots.
Habitat: (presumed) former fallow land with dense young Salix stands sprouting up to 2 metres in height.
Editing: using a FFT-filter, frequencies below 1 kHz were dampened, while 1-8 kHz was slightly amplified. In addition, a brief fade-in and out was added, but no further modifications.
